<span style="font-size:30px;><center>I-Overview</center></span>
{{Underline|FF00FF}}
<div align="center" style="opacity: 1;pointer-events: none; position:fixed; top:0; left:0; right:0; bottom:0;">[[File:Vignette.png|2000px]]</div><div align="center" style="opacity: 0.1;pointer-events: none; position:fixed; z-index:999999; top:0; left:0; right:0; bottom:0;">
[[File:Armastatic.gif|2000px]]</div>
The '''Void Control Unit''', abbreviated as the '''V.C.U.''' and formerly known as '''Backrooms Level Anomaly Center''', is a sub-division of the [[M.E.G.|'''M.E.G.''']] that was founded in 2018. The group was established to look into the cause of the numerous level disappearances, especially negative levels after the events of [[Incident 04-21-18]]. After the [[The Limina Mass Extinction|Limina Mass Extinction]], however, the reasons for the numerous level disappearances were revealed. The division was rebranded and gained a significant presence across '''The Backrooms'''. 

Its purpose is not just to take care of '''The Void's'''unstable behavior, but also to analyse the core functions of our 3 dimensions, '''[[The Frontrooms]]''', '''The Backrooms''', and sometimes, [[The Broken]]. It studies multiple themes such as Leveology, Brokenology, and the Void Theorem. Its main outpost, '''Base Equilibrium''', is located in [[Level 97]] and the sub-division is known for its remarkable breakthroughs in its study of '''The Void''' and the three dimensions. It has taken the charge in documenting the various events that have transpired as '''The Void''' continues to expand.
<span style="font-size:30px;><center>I- Trinity</center></span>
{{Underline|FF00FF}}
The Trinity is a foundational theorem adapted by the V.C.U. about the main three dimensions; [[The Frontrooms|The True Reality]], The Frontrooms, The False Reality, The Backrooms, ane The Shattered Reality, The Broken.

The theorem explains that these realms are the main pillars of reality, thus the name '''Trinity'''. While the way they came to be is up to debate, it is almost globally agreed that reality is composed by 3 realms.
<span style="font-size:30px;><center>III-The Void Theorem</center></span>
{{Underline|FF00FF}}
'''The Void Theorem''' is a principle and the most common explanation in the '''V.C.U.''' for '''The Void's'''. The main basis of this theorem is that The Void is the space in between and surrounding the main three dimensions. The Void is completely devoid of matter. This is due to a mechanism known as [[Nullification]]. When any matter exits one of the dimensions by any methods, it is exposed to The Void. This causes the matter to become unstable and slowly unravel (see [[Nullification]]).

The Void's stability factor is unknown. But as concluded from multiple recordings across the history of human presense in The Backrooms, the stability of The Void has been on a slow decline for millennia prior to the first formation of colonies in the realm, as cases of nullification slowly became more common until in the 21st century, were nullification became a designated threat to both realities.

Much data on The Void has remained ambiguous and up to scientific debate. The Void Theorem remains the most stable and consistent theorem about The Void in The Backrooms.
<span style="font-size:30px;><center>IV-Dual Dimension System</center></span>
{{Underline|FF00FF}}
{{Blurimage|file=FrontrBackrorbitarma.gif|align=center|hovertext=The bond which was thought to be impenetrable, a dance that we thought would last forever|caption=The simulation the V.C.U. uses for representing '''The Frontrooms''' and '''The Backrooms'''.}}
The '''Dual Dimension System''', rarely known as the '''Binary Universe System''', is another principle used by the V.C.U. to explain and represent the relations between The Frontrooms and The Backrooms.
{{Quote|Our universes are total opposites. But like Yin and Yang, they compliment each other. They formed a balance, a balance that for all this time, kept us safe.|████████ ██████, Head of Dynamics Branch.}}
The theory suggests '''The Frontrooms''' and '''The Backrooms''' compliment each other due to their opposing nature. This causes a balance between them that, for the most part, keeps both realities relatively stable, with The Void being what sets the distance between them. '''The Broken''' is thought to be a remnant of The Backrooms that broke off the dimension, forming into a satellite to The Backrooms similar to a moon.
<span style="font-size:30px;><center>V-Brokenology</center></span>
{{Underline|FF00FF}}
'''Brokenology''' is a crucial and intricate genre extensively studied and used in the '''V.C.U.''' Using '''The Broken''' Theorem (BT) as its foundational framework, this discipline delves deep into the complex connection between ''''''The Broken'''''' and '''The Backrooms'''. The theory states that any ''unstable'' matter that strays too far from The Backrooms inevitably splits from that universe and merges into '''The Broken'''.

According to prevailing theories, '''The Broken''' is believed to have severed from The Backrooms due to escalating instability, evolving into a distinct dimension that nevertheless retains prevailing connections to its origin. It acts as a repository for unstable matter originating from The Backrooms and also as a satellite to the dimension, functioning similarly to a moon.

Despite its significance, '''The Broken''' remains a large roadblock in the V.C.U.'s exploration of the three realms. Owing to the paucity of information and limited accessibility to this dimension, much of what is known about '''The Broken''' within V.C.U. circles is primarily conjectural, and the true physics of '''The Broken''' and it's connection with '''The Backrooms''' are not totally confirmed, and remain a mystery.
<span style="font-size:30px;><center>VI-History</center></span>
{{Underline|FF00FF}}
A division similar to this one was planned as far back as the 1960s. However, due to the lack of necessity at the time as The Database played the role of documenting level anomalies, the project was scrapped. But, once negative levels started disappearing in the 2010s, proposals rose for a division dedicated to documenting level anomalies and phenomena. However, [[Temporary Manifestation|Phenomenon 99]] would then be documented and used as an explanation for these anomalies. In 2018, Incident-04-21-18 occurred and was on a much higher scale than any of the previous incidents. This caused the M.E.G. to finally respond by creating the Backrooms Level Anomaly Center. This sub division was very small, and did not have the resources to conduct deep investigations into these anomalies. This would soon be changed, as after [[The Awakening]], M.E.G., in response, started funding the sub-division more, and the group would later be rebranded into the V.C.U. Later that year, Base Equilibrium would be completed and the V.C.U. would gain major presence across The Backrooms.

The group has carried out major evacuations across multiple levels, and has also interviewed multiple wanderers about '''The Void's''' behaviour, any peculiar anomalies and even went as far as to get records of various different entities' behavior when inside a level under '''The Void's''' influence.
<span style="font-size:30px;><center>VII-Documentation</center></span>
{{Underline|FF00FF}}
<center>{{Collapse|num=1|initial=<span style="color:#fdff83">'''> Open Log 001'''</span>|final=<span style="color:#fdff83">'''>Close Log'''</span>|body=<br><div style="background-color: transparent; color: black; margin:1em; font-family: 'Martian Mono'; color:#FFFFFF; padding:15px 20px; border:2px solid #fdff83; border-radius: 10px">
<sup>''The following is a believed conversation between two M.E.G. officials where the first ideas for the V.C.U. were seen.''</sup><br>

"Reports about all these levels disappearing are going wildfire. I don't know how much longer we can cover up all these incidents."

"..Strange. This has been happening for a while, and we still don't know what the fuck is going on."

"We can't keep dismissing everything as regular phenomena, though."

"Then why don't we just get it under control?"

"''How do we put under control what we don't even know?''"

"....That is where my plan comes in hand."
}}
</div>
</center>

<center>{{Collapse|num=2|initial=<span style="color:#fdff83">'''> Open Log 002'''</span>|final=<span style="color:#fdff83">'''>Close Log'''</span>|body=<br><div style="background-color: transparent; color: black; margin:1em; font-family: 'Martian Mono'; color:#FFFFFF; padding:15px 20px; border:2px solid #fdff83; border-radius: 10px">
"After a [[The Awakening|series of events]], regarding the disappearances of multiple levels, we have decided to take action. It has been discovered the reason for these disappearances is due to a recent surge in activity originating from The Void. It has advanced and consumed multiple levels, and now it has officially reached positive levels, with Level 0.1 now destroyed. We will now start taking measure to minimise the amount of casualties caused by these incidents by organising large scale evacuations, transportation of supplies across various bases and <u>'''increased funding on certain branches'''</u>. All bases near the first few positive levels are ordered to immediately evacuate to [[Level 4]] for transportation. A unified response against this new threat will take a lot of time, ''and we don't have much of it''. For now, this new threat is out of our reach, but we will employ survivalist methods to give time for us to come up with ideas, just as we always have."<br>
-The First
}}
</div>
</center>
<span style="font-size:30px;><center>VIII-Bases and Outposts</center></span>
{{Underline|FF00FF}}
<span style="font-size:25px;><center>Base Equilibrium</center></span>
{{Underline|FF00FF}}
{{Blurimage|caption=Base Equilibrium as seen from Level 97.|align=center|file=Equilibriumskyscraper.jpg}}
The main outpost/base for the V.C.U. It is located in [[Level 97]] within one of the tallest skyscrapers, serving as a central hub for information on all three dimensions. Positioned strategically, it offers direct access to [[The Metro]] and [[Base Alpha]], facilitating movement and transportation between key locations.
The base accommodates numerous refugees who have been evacuated from levels consumed by '''The Void''', making it a primary landing site for newcomers entering the level. It is the biggest and most reliable source of information for the 3 dimensions, and The Void, as The Database uses information regarding these dimensions as source for documentation on certain pages. It has more than 5,000 members.
<span style="font-size:25px;><center>Base Binary</center></span>
{{Underline|FF00FF}}
A moderate-sized base located in [[The Hub]]. It used to be a normal M.E.G. base; however, after the rebranding and the increased funds on the V.C.U., this base was given to the sub-division. About 1,223 members.
<span style="font-size:25px;><center>Base Interift</center></span>
{{Underline|FF00FF}}
A small base located in [[The Metro]]. It mostly serves as an entrance to '''Base Equilibrium''', but also serves as a small transport base used to distribute resources across bases and refugees. About 89 members.
<span style="font-size:25px;><center>Base Hetu</center></span>
{{Underline|FF00FF}}
The smallest V.C.U. base. It is located in [[Level 4]] and operates some of the V.C.U.'s database pages. It has about 24 members.
